## MLB Player News from NBC Sports (Rotoworld Player News)

- **Jackson Chourio** – In spite of his minor setback with his hamstring on Monday, Jackson Chourio is starting in left field in Wednesday’s Game 3.
  - URL: https://www.nbcsports.com/fantasy/baseball/player-news?playerNewsId=00000199-c50b-def2-abdb-dd6bc8e80000
- **Cade Horton** – Cade Horton (rib) threw off a mound Tuesday and is expected to do so again Friday.
  - URL: https://www.nbcsports.com/fantasy/baseball/player-news?playerNewsId=00000199-c4da-d94a-a79d-cddf2c300000
- **Paul Toboni** – The Nationals have let go of assistant GMs Eddie Longosz and Mark Scialabba, according to The Athletic.
  - URL: https://www.nbcsports.com/fantasy/baseball/player-news?playerNewsId=00000199-c4c8-d94a-a79d-cdcda8170000
- **Tarik Skubal** – Tarik Skubal will not be available out of the pen for Wednesday’s Game 4 against the Mariners.
